OL,3,CEx-addict who almost gambled his life
OL,4,Caway urges others to get help
OL,6,FMr Peek tearfully recalled writing a
OL,7,Fletter to his wife admitting he'd been
OL,8,F"gambling again" and that she
OL,9,F"deserved better".
OL,11,F"It was essentially eluding to the
OL,12,Ffact that I wanted to not be around
OL,13,Fanymore," Mr Peek told ITV News
OL,14,FCentral. "At that point, it's the
OL,15,Fdamage you're causing to everyone else
OL,16,Flet alone yourself."
OL,18,FMr Peek started gambling in 2010 and
OL,19,Finitially put bets on here and there.
